By Chibuike Nwabuk Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The reported cases of COVID-19 infections Thursday shrunk to 373 compared to the 473 cases recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control report has shown. However, there was a reported increase in death toll from 956 the previous day (Wednesday) to 966 on Thursday. The NCDC in its report released via its twitter handle further revealed that 10 persons died in Nigeria in the last 24 hours of COVID-19 complications. With the new cases of infections reported, the total onfirmed cases in Nigeria now is 48,116 out of which 34,309 have been treated and discharged. The Thursday’s reports released by the health agency are as follow: Lagos-69 Osun-41 Kaduna-40 Oyo-40 FCT-35 Plateau-22 Rivers-19 Kano-17 Ondo-17 Ogun-15 Abia-14 Gombe-12 Imo-9 Enugu-7 Kwara-6 Delta-5 Niger-2 Borno-1 Bauchi-1 Nasarawa-1 48,116 confirmed 34,309 discharged 966 deaths How the states stand:  By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos state, the epicentre of COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria has accounted for 117 infections out of the 423 new confirmed cases recorded in Nigeria on Tuesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has reported. The other 21 states where the novel virus were… August 12, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday said that it has confirmed 354 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total confirmed cases to 45,244. The health agency reported that the 354 new infections were recorded in 17 out of the 36… August 7, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories"